:PROPERTIES:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/print.handbook
Properties

Displays the Properties window. 

You can customize the following print options in
the Properties window:

- Header Page 
     Displays a check mark if you select to
     to print a header page. No check mark is
     is displayed if you select not to print
     a header page.

- Notify When ALL Jobs Are Done 
     You can set audible (beep) and visual (flash)
     notification signals at the completion of all
     print jobs, or when an error occurs. You can
     use either or both as desired.

- Override Print Default Method
     Displays a check mark if you select to over-
     ride the print default. No check mark is
     displayed if you select to use the default
     print method. The default print method is
     displayed in the main panel of the Properties
     window.

Once you customize the print options, you can:

- Apply
     Apply the newly set Printtool properties.

- Save As Defaults
     Save the newly set Printtool properties as
     the default print options.

- Reset
     Erase any new property changes and reinstate
     the last set of applied print options.

