:PMOVERRIDE:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/print.handbook
Print Method Override

To set an override print method, click SELECT on
the box to display a check, then click SELECT on
the Apply button.

The Print Method field is displayed in the main
panel of the Properties window and you can type
in a custom print method.

You can use the following environment variables
to define your custom print method:

$PRINTER - selected printer name
   usage: -d $PRINTER

$COPIES - selected number of copies
   usage: -n $COPIES

$FILE - the file to be printed
   usage: $FILE 

$HEADER - print with or without header
   usage: $HEADER

To define a filter, use the -T option.

The following is an example of a custom print
method using some of the environment variables
listed above:

   lp -d$PRINTER -n$COPIES -Tpostscript $FILE

If this option is disabled, the Print Method
field is invisible.

